1. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper deals with the analysis of a directed network formed by the procedure calls in the Linux Kernel, which can be seen as a data structure. 
2. cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): The paper uses numerical methods to compute the spectrum and eigenstates of the Google matrix of the Linux Kernel network. 
3. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): The paper analyzes the properties of a directed network and its Google matrix, which can be relevant to social and information networks. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper studies the architecture of the Linux Kernel, which can be seen as a complex system that requires control. 
5. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The paper uses computational methods to analyze the Linux Kernel network and its Google matrix, which can be relevant to computational engineering and science.
